SIMPLE: fancier
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fancier
<hw>Fan"ci*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
is governed by fancy.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Not reasoners, but
<xex>fanciers</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who fancies or has a special liking for, or
interest in, a particular object or class or objects; hence, one who
breeds and keeps for sale birds and animals; <as>as, bird
<ex>fancier</ex>, dog <ex>fancier</ex>, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fanciful</ent>⟦br⟧
